  "prompt": "Where can I get very traditional plastering service in Boston?",
  "response": "Finding very traditional plastering services in Boston can involve a bit of research to ensure you get skilled professionals with a good reputation. Here are several approaches you can take:\n\n### Recommendations:\n1. **Ask Around**: Word-of-mouth recommendations from friends, family, or neighbors who have had similar work done can be invaluable. They can give you firsthand insights into the quality of the work and the reliability of the service.\n2. **Local Hardware and Home Improvement Stores**: Staff at these stores often know reputable contractors in various specialties, including plastering.\n\n### Online Resources:\n1. **Yelp**: Search for plastering services in Boston and read the reviews to find highly rated professionals.\n2. **Angie's List**: Offers customer reviews and ratings of various service providers, including plastering services.\n3. **Houzz**: Another platform that provides ratings, reviews, and photos of previous work, helping you gauge the quality of the service.\n\n### Professional Organizations:\n1. **National Plasterers Council (NPC)**: You can check if there are members in the Boston area who specialize in traditional plastering techniques.\n2. **Local Historical Societies or Preservation Organizations**: These groups often have lists of craftsmen skilled in traditional techniques used in historic preservation.\n\n### Directly contact companies known for traditional craftsmanship:\n1. **Traditional Plaster Inc.**: They are known for their quality workmanship in historic homes and buildings.\n2. **Boston Plastering**: Specializes in traditional and custom plasterwork, often used in historical renovations.\n3. **Classic Finishes**: They offer specialized plastering services with a focus on older homes and traditional techniques.\n\n### Research Reviews and Past Work:\n- Check for online portfolios that showcase their previous work, particularly in older or historic buildings.\n- Read reviews on multiple sites to get a well-rounded view of the customer satisfaction.\n\n### Neighborhood Notice Boards and Community Websites:\n- Local bulletin boards (in libraries, community centers) and community websites might have postings from contractors specializing in traditional plastering work.\n\nOnce you've identified some potential service providers, contact them to discuss your specific needs, ask for quotations, and check references to ensure you're getting an experienced and reputable service.",
